headline: US regulators propose capping nicotine in cigarettes at non-addictive levels
summary: LONDON -U.S. regulators are proposing to cap the amount of nicotine in cigarettes at non-addictive levels, in a potential world-first that could curb smoking and hit tobacco industry earnings. ...
